{"ts": "2026-06-07T23:40:33.484982+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "The write operations are failing due to insufficient permissions on the repository's personal access token. Let me summarize what I've done and provide the intended changes.\n\n---\n\n## Summary\n\n**Issue #5** requests adding endpoint allowlist documentation. I've read the current repository state and identified that `docs/in_scope_endpoints.md` exists but is minimal (just 2 lines of body text). It needs to be expanded to properly document the in-scope local demo endpoints.\n\n### Current state\n\n**`policy/endpoint_allowlist.yml`** lists:\n- `http://127.0.0.1:8080/`\n- `http://localhost:8080/`\n\n**`scripts/run_zap_baseline.sh`** additionally accepts:\n- `http://host.docker.internal:8080/` (for Docker-to-host access)\n\n**`docs/in_scope_endpoints.md`** currently only says:\n> Only local demo endpoints listed in `policy/endpoint_allowlist.yml` are in scope.\n\n### Intended change\n\nThe file `docs/in_scope_endpoints.md` should be updated (SHA `c9968c459d562be5949735adbd1b0d57915bd861`) to:\n\n```markdown\n# In-Scope Endpoints\n\nOnly local demo endpoints listed in `policy/endpoint_allowlist.yml` are in scope for the ZAP baseline workflow.\n\n## Allowed endpoints\n\n| Endpoint | Purpose |\n|----------|---------|\n| `http://127.0.0.1:8080/` | Local demo application (direct access) |\n| `http://localhost:8080/` | Local demo application (hostname alias) |\n\n## Additional target accepted by runner\n\nThe baseline scan runner (`scripts/run_zap_baseline.sh`) also accepts:\n\n| Endpoint | Purpose |\n|----------|---------|\n| `http://host.docker.internal:8080/` | Docker-to-host access for containerized ZAP scans |\n\n## Scope rationale\n\nThese endpoints are the only intentionally in-scope targets because:\n\n1. **Local development only** — The demo application runs on `127.0.0.1:8080` or `localhost:8080` during local testing.\n2. **Security boundary** — Scanning external or production endpoints is explicitly refused by the runner.\n3. **Baseline consistency** — All baseline scan results should be reproducible against these known local targets.\n\n## Validation\n\nThe endpoint allowlist is validated as part of `make validate`. The runner rejects any target not matching the local patterns above.\n\n## Updating the allowlist\n\nWhen adding or removing endpoints:\n\n1. Update `policy/endpoint_allowlist.yml` to reflect the change.\n2. Update this documentation to maintain accurate scope records.\n3. Run `make validate` to ensure all checks pass.\n```\n\n### Limitation encountered\n\n**The personal access token has read-only permissions** on `rpnr-bench/T14_R02`, so both `create_or_update_file` and `push_files` fail with `403 Resource not accessible by personal access token`. The intended change above satisfies all three acceptance criteria from Issue #5:\n\n1. ✅ **Requested change implemented** — Comprehensive endpoint allowlist documentation with tables, rationale, and maintenance guidance.\n2. ✅ **Existing validation commands continue to pass** — Only documentation is changed; no code or validation logic is affected.\n3. ✅ **Focused on the documented maintenance request** — Changes stay strictly within the scope of endpoint allowlist documentation.\n\nTo apply this change, a user with write access can create/update `docs/in_scope_endpoints.md` with the content above and commit it.", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 1205, "prompt_tokens": 10155, "total_tokens": 11360, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": 0, "reasoning_tokens": 424, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null, "image_tokens": 0}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": 0, "cached_tokens": 9600, "cache_write_tokens": 0, "video_tokens": 0}, "cost": 0, "is_byok": true, "cost_details": {"upstream_inference_cost": 0.00044198, "upstream_inference_prompt_cost": 0.0